to%20ensure%20they%20had%20enough%20cash%20on%20hand.%20They%20didn't%20know%20exactly%20what%20the%20severance%20package%20would%20look%20like%2C%20so%20they%20wanted%20to%20be%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20layoff%20hit%2C%20Hendersen%20learned%20she'd%20continue%20receiving%20paychecks%20through%20late%20August%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20lump-sum%20severance%20payment%20based%20on%20her%20years%20of%20service.%20With%20that%20information%2C%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20analyzed%20their%20budget%2C%20determined%20how%20far%20their%20savings%20would%20take%20them%2C%20and%20identified%20expenses%20they%20could%20cut.%20She%20said%20the%20process%20was%20stressful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20very%20much%20a%20sense%20of%20stunning%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226537cf33-1914-41e8-b1c4-eebe30a0dadc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20a%20job%20without%20applying%20for%20one%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20reaching%20out%20to%20colleagues%20and%20preparing%20financially%2C%20Hendersen%20hoped%20to%20make%20the%20transition%20from%20Microsoft%20a%20little%20smoother.%20But%20she%20wanted%20to%20take%20some%20time%20to%20decompress%20and%20get%20organized%20before%20beginning%20her%20job%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20had%20been%2015%20years%20since%20I'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-microsoft-engineer-resume-updates-every-few-months-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eupdated%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20any%20meaningful%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20standardized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-to-write-memorable-cover-letter-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecover%20letters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20didn't%20have%20all%20the%20little%20stories%20prepared%20that%20you're%20supposed%20to%20tell%20about%20yourself%20in%20interviews.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Hendersen%20said%20she%20didn't%20decompress%20quite%20as%20much%20as%20she'd%20intended.%20After%20posting%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20friends%20and%20former%20colleagues%20began%20reaching%20out%20about%20job%20opportunities%2C%20leading%20to%20informal%20conversations%20about%20whether%20they%20could%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20like%20this%20ocean%20of%20warm%20hugs%20and%20kindness%20that%20came%20from%20people%20who%20were%20here%20to%20help%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupport%20also%20came%20from%20the%20other%20laid-off%20Microsoft%20colleagues%20she'd%20organized%20in%20a%20Teams%20chat.%20Before%20losing%20access%20to%20their%20internal%20chat%2C%20the%20group%20transitioned%20to%20Discord%2C%20where%20they%20shared%20job%20opportunities%2C%20helped%20each%20other%20prepare%20for%20interviews%2C%20vented%20their%20frustrations%2C%20and%20celebrated%20their%20successes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Hendersen%20was%20finding%20opportunities%20through%20her%20network%2C%20she%20generally%20avoided%20the%20traditional%20application%20route.%20In%20total%2C%20she%20thinks%20she%20may%20have%20formally%20applied%20to%20one%20role.%20Relying%20on%20her%20network%20felt%20more%20manageable%2C%20especially%20since%2C%20after%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20out%20of%20the%20job%20market%2C%20she%20wasn't%20sure%20how%20to%20navigate%20online%20job%20searching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20she%20would%20share%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20with%20a%20connection%2C%20who%20would%20then%20refer%20her%20for%20a%20role.%20A%20recruiter%20would%20follow%20up%20to%20begin%20the%20process.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20someone%20would%20flag%20an%20opening%2C%20and%20she'd%20message%20the%20recruiter%20directly%2C%20rather%20than%20applying%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20roles%20that%20was%20recommended%20to%20her%20was%20a%20user%20experience%20researcher%20position%20at%20Meta.%20Someone%20she%20knew%20at%20the%20company%20told%20her%20about%20the%20opening%2C%20which%20was%20similar%20to%20her%20role%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20where%20she'd%20conducted%20studies%20to%20evaluate%20how%20players%20interacted%20with%20games%20in%20development.%20The%20Meta%20role%20was%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-recruits-reality-labs-restructuring-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReality%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company's%20hardware%20and%20virtual%20reality%20division%2C%20and%20allowed%20her%20to%20work%20from%20Meta's%20Seattle%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHendersen%20said%20the%20position%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20and%20after%20her%20connection%20referred%20her%2C%20she%20landed%20an%20interview.%20In%20late%20August%2C%20she%20received%20a%20job%20offer%20and%20started%20full-time%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a42ecd31-8fdd-4d32-a2ae-32758abbf0ad%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20respond%20to%20a%20layoff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHendersen%20said%20she%20came%20away%20from%20her%20job%20search%20with%20a%20few%20takeaways.%20First%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20develop%20a%20library%20of%20stories%20from%20your%20career%20that%20you%20can%20use%20in%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20done%20amazing%20things%20that%20people%20should%20be%20really%20impressed%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20can%20you%20remember%20them%20in%20the%20moment%3F%20That's%20so%20hard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20recommends%20practicing%20how%20to%20tell%20those%20stories%2C%20especially%20to%20people%20who%20aren't%20in%20your%20field.%20When%20she%20interviewed%20at%20Meta%2C%20not%20everyone%20she%20spoke%20with%20came%20from%20the%20gaming%20world.%20That%20meant%20she%20had%20to%20explain%20her%20past%20work%20in%20a%20way%20that%20resonated%20with%20interviewers%20who%20didn't%20have%20the%20same%20level%20of%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20her%20biggest%20takeaway%